      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UNIVERSAL IMPACT (2) knocked over the maiden in good fashion here 26 days ago when sitting handy and getting the job done by 1.1L. The form out of that race has been strong and the claim of Cheung comes in handy. Can find the front again and be very hard to run down. REDRYE (1) settled last at Albany last time out and got over the top to score by 1.3L in a strong performance. While it was her maiden win, she was racing in a bm58+. Drawn the inside now with Martinan claiming 3kgs and another forward showing is on the cards. YALDA NIGHT (3) flew home to just miss in a photo finish at Narrogin last start in a BM44+. The better draw this time can see him sit a touch closer and Nottle's claim sees him down in the weights. Can feature in the finish again. BUCKLAND (4) wasn't beaten far last start and has claims. PRETEY ROYAL (6) can be in the finish from a good draw.",
